<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Optionyze | Delta Neutral Live Trading</title>
    <%- include('partials/brand-head') %>
    <style>
        :root { color-scheme: dark; --bg: #050816; --panel: rgba(10, 18, 38, 0.82); --text: #f3f6ff; --muted: #a7b2d4; --line: rgba(162, 180, 228, 0.18); --accent-soft: rgba(80, 227, 194, 0.12); --shadow: 0 28px 80px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35); }
        * { box-sizing: border-box; }
        body { margin: 0; font-family: "Segoe UI", "Trebuchet MS", sans-serif; background: radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(80, 227, 194, 0.14), transparent 28%), radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(242, 182, 90, 0.12), transparent 26%), linear-gradient(180deg, #040714 0%, #08101f 55%, #050816 100%); color: var(--text); }
        a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
        .shell { width: min(1180px, calc(100% - 40px)); margin: 0 auto; }
        .topbar { position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 20; backdrop-filter: blur(16px); background: rgba(5, 8, 22, 0.72); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06); }
        .nav { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px; min-height: 78px; }
        .brand { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.18em; font-size: 0.95rem; }
        .brand-mark { width: 48px; height: 48px; display: block; object-fit: contain; flex: 0 0 auto; }
        .nav-links, .auth-links { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 18px; }
        .nav-links a, .auth-links a, .auth-links button { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; background: none; border: 0; cursor: pointer; font: inherit; }
        .nav-links a:hover, .auth-links a:hover, .auth-links button:hover { color: var(--text); }
        .button, .button-secondary { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; min-height: 44px; padding: 0 18px; border-radius: 999px; font-weight: 600; transition: transform 0.18s ease, box-shadow 0.18s ease; }
        .button { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #50e3c2, #7dd3fc); color: #05101d; box-shadow: 0 18px 36px rgba(80, 227, 194, 0.18); }
        .button-secondary { background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04); color: var(--text); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08); }
        .hero { padding: 92px 0 56px; }
        .hero-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.2fr) minmax(320px, 0.8fr); gap: 28px; }
        .eyebrow { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; padding: 8px 14px; border-radius: 999px; background: var(--accent-soft); border: 1px solid rgba(80, 227, 194, 0.18); color: #9cf4df; font-size: 0.82rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; }
        h1 { margin: 20px 0 16px; font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 5.8vw, 5.4rem); line-height: 0.98; letter-spacing: -0.04em; }
        .hero-copy { max-width: 720px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 1.08rem; line-height: 1.78; }
        .hero-actions { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 14px; margin: 28px 0 36px; }
        .metrics { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 14px; }
        .metric, .feature, .callout, .section-card { background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 24px; box-shadow: var(--shadow); }
        .metric { padding: 18px 18px 20px; }
        .metric-label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.82rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
        .metric-value { margin-top: 10px; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; }
        .hero-panel { position: relative; overflow: hidden; padding: 26px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(13, 24, 49, 0.96), rgba(7, 13, 28, 0.96)); }
        .panel-copy, .feature p, .section-card p, .section-card li, .callout p, .section-heading p { color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.72; }
        .panel-list { display: grid; gap: 12px; }
        .panel-item { padding: 14px 16px; border-radius: 18px; background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06); }
        main { padding-bottom: 72px; }
        .section { padding: 34px 0; }
        .section-heading { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: end; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
        .section-heading h2 { margin: 0; font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.6rem); letter-spacing: -0.03em; }
        .feature-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 18px; }
        .feature, .section-card { padding: 24px; }
        .feature-tag { display: inline-flex; padding: 7px 12px; border-radius: 999px; background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04); color: #bfd1ff; font-size: 0.78rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; }
        .feature h3, .section-card h3, .callout h3 { margin: 16px 0 10px; }
        .two-col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(320px, 0.9fr); gap: 18px; }
        .section-card ul { padding-left: 18px; margin: 12px 0 0; }
        .callout { padding: 28px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(80, 227, 194, 0.12), rgba(242, 182, 90, 0.12)); }
        .footer-note { margin-top: 28px; color: rgba(167, 178, 212, 0.72); font-size: 0.92rem; text-align: center; }
        .auth-form { display: inline; margin: 0; }
        .notice { margin: 18px 0 0; padding: 12px 14px; border-radius: 16px; background: rgba(242, 182, 90, 0.12); border: 1px solid rgba(242, 182, 90, 0.24); color: #ffd79d; }
        @media (max-width: 980px) { .hero-grid, .two-col, .feature-grid, .metrics { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .section-heading { align-items: start; flex-direction: column; } }
        @media (max-width: 760px) { .nav { flex-wrap: wrap; padding: 14px 0; } .nav-links { order: 3; width: 100%; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; padding-bottom: 6px; overflow-x: auto; } .auth-links { margin-left: auto; } .hero { padding-top: 64px; } h1 { line-height: 1.04; } }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header class="topbar">
        <div class="shell nav">
            <a class="brand" href="/"><img class="brand-mark" src="/brand/optionyze-logo-v4-dark-blue.png" alt="Optionyze" /><span>OPTIONYZE</span></a>
            <nav class="nav-links"><a href="#strategy">Strategy</a><a href="#execution">Execution</a><a href="#risk">Risk Control</a><a href="#platform">Platform</a></nav>
            <div class="auth-links">
                <% if (currentAccount) { %>
                    <a href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a>
                    <form class="auth-form" action="/auth/signout" method="post"><button type="submit">Sign Out</button></form>
                <% } else { %>
                    <a href="/signin">Sign In</a>
                    <a class="button-secondary" href="/signup">Sign Up</a>
                <% } %>
            </div>
        </div>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section class="hero">
            <div class="shell hero-grid">
                <div>
                    <div class="eyebrow">Server-side delta neutral execution</div>
                    <h1>Run one live delta neutral strategy with cleaner risk control and server-side continuity.</h1>
                    <p class="hero-copy">Optionyze is now centered around a live delta neutral options strategy that combines short CE and PE execution, live futures hedging, SL and TP re-entry logic, and persistent server-side monitoring. The focus is no longer broad experimentation. It is one operational trading workflow that can stay disciplined even when browsers close or one server drops out.</p>
                    <% if (currentAccount && currentAccount.mustChangePassword) { %><div class="notice">Your admin account is active. Please change the temporary password before using the app.</div><% } %>
                    <div class="hero-actions">
                        <% if (currentAccount) { %>
                            <a class="button" href="<%= currentAccount.mustChangePassword ? '/account/change-password' : '/dashboard' %>">Open Dashboard</a>
                        <% } else { %>
                            <a class="button" href="/signup">Start With Optionyze</a>
                        <% } %>
                        <a class="button-secondary" href="#strategy">Explore The Strategy</a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="metrics"><div class="metric"><div class="metric-label">Execution Model</div><div class="metric-value">Live Server Runner</div></div><div class="metric"><div class="metric-label">Storage Layer</div><div class="metric-value"><%= storageMode %></div></div><div class="metric"><div class="metric-label">Strategy Focus</div><div class="metric-value">Delta Neutral</div></div></div>
                </div>
                <aside class="hero-panel"><div class="panel-title">What this strategy runner is built to solve</div><p class="panel-copy">Manual delta neutral management gets messy fast: option legs drift, hedges lag, exits are missed, and outages create confusion. Optionyze is being shaped to make that workflow repeatable.</p><div class="panel-list"><div class="panel-item"><strong>Persistent live execution</strong><span> The strategy cycle runs on the server so positions, hedges, and protective checks do not depend on one open browser tab.</span></div><div class="panel-item"><strong>Recovery-aware design</strong><span> Survival state, takeover flow, and server-side ownership reduce the risk of losing control during infrastructure issues.</span></div><div class="panel-item"><strong>Account-level control</strong><span> Each account can keep separate API profiles, quantity choices, Telegram alerts, and operating preferences.</span></div></div></aside>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="section" id="strategy"><div class="shell"><div class="section-heading"><h2>One strategy, managed deeply</h2><p>Instead of spreading across many half-built workflows, Optionyze is now concentrating on one live strategy and making it operationally strong: entries, live hedging, protective exits, re-entry behavior, recovery state, and admin visibility.</p></div><div class="feature-grid"><article class="feature"><span class="feature-tag">Entry structure</span><h3>Short CE and PE with live controls</h3><p>The strategy is designed around selling both option legs with quantity, expiry, and delta settings that stay configurable per account.</p></article><article class="feature"><span class="feature-tag">Adjustment logic</span><h3>Futures hedge plus SL and TP rules</h3><p>As total delta drifts or individual option legs hit protection levels, the runner can hedge, close, and re-enter without waiting for manual intervention.</p></article><article class="feature"><span class="feature-tag">Operator clarity</span><h3>Built for real monitoring</h3><p>The page, event stream, admin controls, and recovery tooling are all being shaped around one live workflow that needs to be understood quickly.</p></article></div></div></section>
        <section class="section" id="execution"><div class="shell two-col"><article class="section-card"><h3>How the live cycle works</h3><p>The strategy keeps watching current positions, option deltas, futures hedge needs, and configured protection levels. The important part is not just the trade idea. It is the repeatable server-side cycle that keeps acting on that idea.</p><ul><li>Entry settings define expiry selection, lot size, and delta targets.</li><li>Live monitoring checks hedge thresholds and option SL or TP conditions.</li><li>Closed-position refresh and recovery totals help reconcile exchange-side results.</li></ul></article><article class="section-card"><h3>Why server-side execution matters here</h3><p>A delta neutral strategy can break down if the operator misses one hedge or one protective exit. Moving the cycle to the server makes the workflow less dependent on a device staying open.</p><ul><li><strong>Persistent ownership:</strong> one server owns the live cycle at a time.</li><li><strong>Survival mode:</strong> live management can continue through primary database outages.</li><li><strong>Takeover flow:</strong> standby infrastructure can resume control if the active owner fails.</li></ul></article></div></section>
        <section class="section" id="risk"><div class="shell"><div class="section-heading"><h2>Risk control is part of the product, not a side note</h2><p>This strategy is being built around the assumption that live positions need defensive structure. Quantity sizing, delta hedging, option-level SL and TP, and operational recovery all matter as much as the initial entry.</p></div><div class="two-col"><article class="section-card"><h3>What the operator can control</h3><p>Users can shape the strategy with expiry rules, start quantity, hedge preferences, closed-position recovery updates, and Telegram alerts for meaningful engine and trading events.</p><ul><li>Live sizing can be estimated from available balance.</li><li>Alert defaults focus on engine stops, engine errors, futures and option activity, and SL triggers.</li><li>Admin tools help identify ownership, primary mode, survival mode, and handback actions.</li></ul></article><article class="callout"><h3>What makes this more than a simple signal page</h3><p>The real value is not just showing a trading screen. It is combining execution, recovery state, admin visibility, and exchange-aware event logging into one workflow that can actually be operated during live market hours.</p></article></div></div></section>
        <section class="section" id="platform"><div class="shell"><div class="section-heading"><h2>Where the platform is headed</h2><p>The immediate path is a stable server-side app that can host multiple user profiles, keep strategy state on the server, and separate live trading from paper experimentation. Sign In and Sign Up flows are now the account foundation for the next layers.</p></div><div class="feature-grid"><article class="feature"><span class="feature-tag">For users</span><h3>Account-based access</h3><p>Each user can maintain their own credentials, capital preferences, strategy permissions, and notification channels.</p></article><article class="feature"><span class="feature-tag">For operations</span><h3>Runner management</h3><p>Admin controls can start, stop, audit, and inspect individual strategy runners without relying on per-user browser sessions.</p></article><article class="feature"><span class="feature-tag">For strategy growth</span><h3>Clear product lanes</h3><p>Live Covered Call, paper-trading Greeks workflows, and user management can evolve independently while still sharing one platform foundation.</p></article></div><div class="footer-note">Optionyze is under active build. User onboarding now begins with Sign Up and Sign In, and admin-led user management will follow next.</div></div></section>
        <section class="section" id="platform"><div class="shell"><div class="section-heading"><h2>Where the platform is headed</h2><p>The immediate direction is to keep strengthening this single live strategy: better operator visibility, cleaner runner ownership, stronger account controls, and tighter recovery during infrastructure issues.</p></div><div class="feature-grid"><article class="feature"><span class="feature-tag">For users</span><h3>Cleaner live execution</h3><p>Each account can keep its own API profiles, notification setup, quantity choices, and operating preferences inside one consistent workflow.</p></article><article class="feature"><span class="feature-tag">For operations</span><h3>Better admin visibility</h3><p>Ownership state, survival state, server takeover, and handback controls are being surfaced so live positions can be operated with less guesswork.</p></article><article class="feature"><span class="feature-tag">For the product</span><h3>Depth before breadth</h3><p>Instead of jumping into many strategy pages, Optionyze is now focusing on making Delta Neutral live trading operationally solid first.</p></article></div><div class="footer-note">Optionyze is under active build. The current product focus is a single live delta neutral workflow with stronger server-side continuity and account-level controls.</div></div></section>
    </main>
</body>
</html>
